  "body": "The python team report that on this transaction \r\n`retesteth -t GeneralStateTests/stTransactionTest -- --singletest ValueOverflow --verbosity RPC --clients default --singlenet Merge`\r\nt8n inputs:\r\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/1WpZz9k0o5DZX70AWE98gFNhgijoiNL6H/view?usp=sharing\r\n\r\nlive web trace:\r\nhttp://retesteth.ethdevops.io/web/index.php?gtests=stTransactionTest&singletest=ValueOverflow&clients=t8ntool&snetwork=Merge&vmtrace=none&verbosity=RPC&trd=&trg=&trv=\r\n\r\nThe geth t8n is given a malicious tx rlp with value field over 256 bit value. and it seems it still tries to calculate the gas/price requirements for the execution and report that not enough funds in the senders account. \r\nInstead it must throw transaction parse error or smth. becaues the value field is not allowed to be that high. \r\n\r\n",
